info.description: # Customers Collection ## Summary This collection was designed to test and validate responses from the Customers API, which reads and updates customer-specific data within the Acme Co database. ## How to use this collection This collection is meant to run automated tests in conjunction with the [Customers API](https://cs-demo.postman.co/workspace/c06eaed9-1cdc-4b3e-934b-3985817a71fc/api/cfd9425f-2989-4f81-87e0-bea133996be4?branch=main) which is also available in this workspace (under APIs > Customers). You will notice there are _Collection-level_ tests, along with _Request-specific_ **Tests** and **Pre-request Scripts**. These scripts are meant to either support or validate required behavior in this API during the **Scheduled** **Collection** runs, **Monitor** runs, and **CI/CD pipeline** runs (which are triggered by pushes to the `main` or `dev` branches in our [linked GitHub repository](https://github.com/postman-solutions-eng/customersAutomatedTesting/tree/main)). ## Scoping The collections, folders, and requests in this workspace all have their own scopes, contained within the scope of the workspace itself. You can view more information on leveraging scopes within Postman scripts in our [Learning Center documentation](https://learning.postman.com/docs/sending-requests/variables/#variable-scopes).
